<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>hold forth on something • hold forth something</xh5><p> <i>hold forth on something—</i>speak at length about smth.: Mrs. Price was <u>holding forth on</u> the subject of servantdom.</p><p> <i>hold forth something—</i>1. expose smth. to view: He <u>held forth</u> the paper on which he had written something. 2. offer or promise smth.: We present ourselves to you as allies who <u>hold forth</u> to you the advantages of British protection.</p> </entry>
